18-YEAR-OLD BLUES GUITARIST

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:24.000
JONNY LANG FILLS CONCERT HALLS

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.000
WITH FANS WHO CAN'T BELIEVE WHAT

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:28.000
HE CAN DO.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:29.000
I THINK HE'S GREAT.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:29.000
AMAZING FO

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.000
GO AHEAD AND LIE TO ME *

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:33.000
Reporter: TWO YEARS AGO, LANG

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.000
HAD AMERICA'S NUMBER ONE BLUES

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.000
ALBUM.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:37.000
HE SAYS WHEN HE WAS 13,

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:38.000
HE PLAYED HIS GUITAR 12 HOURS

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:40.000
*

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:42.000
I DIDN'T CARE ABOUT ANYTHING

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:43.000
ELSE BUT PLAYING, YOU KNOW,

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:45.000
LIKE ANYTHING.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:47.000
**

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:49.000
Reporter: AND AT 18, JONNY

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:50.000
ASSUMES HE'LL HAVE THIS ENERGY

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:53.000
ALL HIS LIFE.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:56.000
DO YOU THINK MAYBE YOU'LL JUST

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:57.000
GET LESS INSPIRED IN 10 YEARS,

00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:58.000
20 YEARS?

00:05:58.000 --> 00:05:59.000
LESS ENERGETIC?

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.000
I ALWAYS USE B.B. KING

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:01.000
AS AN EXAMPLE FOR THIS, LIKE,

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.000
YOU WATCH HIM AND THAT.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:04.000
HE'S 74 NOW, AND HE DOESN'T LOOK

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.000
LIKE HE'S LOST AN OUNCE

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
OF ANYTHING.

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.000
Reporter: IF WE ASKED

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:10.000
B.B. KING, YOU'D THINK HE'D SAY

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.000
HE'S AS PASSIONATE NOW AS HE WAS

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.000
WHEN HE WAS YOUR AGE?

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:15.000
I DON'T THINK THAT IT'S LESS

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:19.000
OF AN ENERGY.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:23.000
OH, WHAT A WONDERFUL GUY.

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.000
BUT NO, I DO NOT HAVE THE ENERGY

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:28.000
TODAY THAT I HAD WHEN I WAS 17.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:29.000
* I'VE BEEN AROUND

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:52.000
A LONG TIME,

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:52.000
A PERFECT 10!

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:53.000
Reporter: I THINK YOU CAN

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:55.000
EVEN SEE THE DIFFERENCE

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.000
IN THE SMILES.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.000
WE ADULTS RARELY LET IT OUT LIKE

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:01.000
THIS, OUR SMILES AREN'T

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:01.000
THIS BIG.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:02.000
IT'S WONDERFUL TO WATCH

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:04.000
A TEENAGER LIKE VENUS WILLIAMS

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:05.000
WIN A MATCH.

00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:08.000
AND TEENS HAVE BEEN SETTING ALL

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:13.000
ASTER THAN

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:15.000
WHEN HE WAS A TEEN.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.000
SOME SAY THE TEENS SET RECORDS

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:17.000
BECAUSE THEIR PASSION MAKES THEM

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.000
WORK HARDER.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.000
18-YEAR-OLD AL HARRINGTON LOVES

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.000
BASKETBALL SO MUCH, HE WORKS OUT

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:25.000
SEVEN HOURS A DAY.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:26.000
HE CAN'T GET ENOUGH.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:29.000
AL!

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:30.000
Reporter: BECAUSE HE GETS

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:31.000
SO MUCH JOY OUT OF THE GAME.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:33.000
ONCE I GO PAST A PERSON, IT'S

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.000
JUST LIKE SUNSHINE.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:36.000
YOU JUST SEE THE SUN UP THERE.

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:37.000
AND IT'S ALL LIT UP.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:40.000
HARRINGTON, ALL ALONE,

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:41.000
BADA BOOM!

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:42.000
Reporter: THIS YEAR, HE WAS

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:43.000
A FIRST-ROUND DRAFT PICK

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:44.000
IN THE NBA, AHEAD OF HUNDREDS

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.000
OF COLLEGE PLAYERS.

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:47.000
MAYBE HE GOT THIS GOOD

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.000
BECAUSE HE WAS TAKING

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:52.000
2,000 PRACTICE SHOTS EVERY DAY.

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:53.000
JUST HOW MUCH MORE ENERGY DO

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:56.000
TEENS HAVE?

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.000
WE RAN SOME TESTS AT THIS SPORTS

00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.000
MEDICINE CLINIC.

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.000
BEN, YOUR TASK TODAY IS

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:02.000
TO KEEP UP WITH THE TREADMILL.

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:03.000
Reporter: FIRST, WE INVITED

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:05.000
18-YEAR-OLD BEN MULLIGAN TO TAKE

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:06.000
AN AEROBIC TEST.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:08.000
IT MEASURES HOW MUCH OXYGEN

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:10.000
YOU DELIVER TO YOUR MUSCLES.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:11.000
WHILE THE TESTERS MAKE YOU RUN

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:13.000
FASTER AND MORE UPHILL.

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:15.000
THAT'S IT, HANG IN A LITTLE

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.000
BIT MORE.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:17.000
COME ON.

00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:18.000
Reporter: THE RESEARCHERS

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:19.000
HERE SAY SIMPLY BECAUSE BEN'S

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:20.000
A TEENAGER, HIS HEART CAN PUMP

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:21.000
MORE BLOOD AND PROCESS MORE

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:22.000
OXYGEN THAN MINE.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.000
THEY HAVE HIM RUN UNTIL HE CAN'T

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:27.000
RUN ANYMORE.

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:28.000
REALLY GOOD TEST.

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
THAT WAS A REAL MAXIMAL TEST.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:33.000
Reporter: NOW, I EXERCISE

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:33.000
REGULARLY.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:34.000
I THOUGHT I COULD DO AS WELL

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:35.000
AS A TEEN ON THIS TEST,

00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:36.000
BUT THE PHYSIOLOGIST HERE SAYS,

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:38.000
"NO WAY."

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.000
YOU ASSUME HIS BODY WILL JUST DO

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:40.000
THINGS MINE CAN'T.

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:43.000
I CAN GUARANTEE IT.

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:44.000
Reporter: SURE ENOUGH, WHEN

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:47.000
IT WAS MY TURN ON THE MACHINE,

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:48.000
THEY COULD SEE THE DIFFERENCE.

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:49.000
JOHN, YOU'RE SOUNDING

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:50.000
A LITTLE BIT HEAVIER

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:51.000
ON YOUR FEET THAN BEN DID

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:52.000
AT THIS POINT.

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:54.000
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.000
[ MUMBLING ]

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.000
Reporter: I GAVE UP SEVERAL

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:58.000
MINUTES SOONER THAN BEN DID.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:01.000
KEEP WALKING.

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:02.000
COME ON, KEEP WALKING.

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:02.000
DON'T STOP.

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:04.000
IT'S ONLY ONE MILE AN HOUR.

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:06.000
Reporter: THE TEST SHOWS HOW

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:07.000
INEFFICIENT MY BLOOD AND OXYGEN

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:08.000
USE IS COMPARED TO BEN'S.

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:10.000
ON A QUICK LOOK-SEE,

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:11.000
ABOUT 66% OF WHAT BEN DID.

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:12.000
Reporter: I COULD HAVE

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:13.000
TOUGHED IT OUT LONGER,

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:20.000
BUT I DIDN'T WANT TO SHOW

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:21.000
NADIA COMANECI?

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:22.000
DO A JUMP.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.000
Reporter: SHE'S NOW 37 AND

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:26.000
HELPING COACH FUTURE POTENTIAL

00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:28.000
OLYMPIANS LIKE 15-YEAR-OLD

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.000
ANGELA BEAM.

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:31.000
BUT NADIA'S STILL FIT, SHE WORKS

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:33.000
OUT EVERY DAY.

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:34.000
BUT STILL, IT QUICKLY BECAME

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:35.000
CLEAR THAT BEATING ANGELA

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:36.000
WOULDN'T BE EASY.

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:38.000
THERE'S NO WAY I'M GOING

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:39.000
TO MAKE THIS.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:40.000
TOO HARD.

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:41.000
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:42.000
IT'S JUST WALKING.

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.000
I JUST HAVE A GOOD VISION

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:46.000
OF KNOWING WHAT I CAN DO.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:47.000
YOU PROBABLY WANT TO JOG NOW.

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:49.000
Reporter: SURE ENOUGH, EVEN

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:52.000
THE WINNER OF FIVE GOLD MEDALS

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:52.000
COULDN'T DO WHAT THE TEEN

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:53.000
COULD DO.

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.000
I PROBABLY WANT TO STOP NOW.

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:55.000
Reporter: THOUGH SHE TRIED

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:56.000
HARD.

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:57.000
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO LOSE

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:58.000
TO A TEENAGER?

00:09:58.000 --> 00:09:59.000
OF COURSE NOT.

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:00.000
WOULD YOU?

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:01.000
Reporter: A TEEN'S BODY JUST

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:03.000
WORKS BETTER.

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:05.000
SHE CAN JUST PROCESS THE OXYGEN

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:05.000
INTO HER BODY BETTER.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:06.000
RIGHT.

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:07.000
RIGHT.

00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:08.000
SHE CAN TAKE IT IN.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:09.000
SHE CAN MOVE IT AROUND THE BODY

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:11.000
FASTER, AND SHE CAN UTILIZE IT

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:12.000
BETTER.

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:14.000
Reporter: WHEN DO WE PEAK?

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:15.000
WELL, FOR MEN, THE PEAKING

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:17.000
SEEMS TO OCCUR SOMEPLACE BETWEEN

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:20.000
THE AGES OF 17 TO 20,

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:22.000
WITHOUT ANY ADDITIONAL TRAINING.

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:23.000
FOR WOMEN, THAT HAPPENS EARLIER,

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:24.000
SOME PLACE CLOSER TO THE AGE

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:26.000
OF AROUND 13 TO 15.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.000
Reporter: PEAK FOR A WOMAN IS

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:29.000
BY 15?

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:30.000
YEAH.

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:31.000
IT SEEMS THAT THAT'S THE POINT

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:34.000
WHERE MOST THINGS ARE MAXED OUT.

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:35.000
Reporter: AND 18, 19 FOR MEN?

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:36.000
FOR THE MEN.

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:37.000
Reporter: IT'S

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:38.000
OVER BY THE TIME YOU'RE 19.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:50.000
IT'S OVER

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:52.000
AND THAT'S WHY AL HARRINGTON IS

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:55.000
NERVOUSLY LIFTING WEIGHTS.

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:56.000
PASSION IS NOT ENOUGH.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:58.000
YOU SEEN THEM GUYS ON THE NBA

00:10:58.000 --> 00:10:59.000
FLOOR?

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:03.000
I MEAN, THEY ARE HUGE!

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:04.000
THEY'RE GROPE MEN.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:05.000
MOST OF 'EM, YOU KNOW, 25 AND

00:11:05.000 --> 00:11:06.000
OLDER AND I'M ONLY 18.

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:07.000
Reporter: STILL AT 18,

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:08.000
IN MANY WAYS, WE'RE AS FULL

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:09.000
OF PASSION AND ENERGY AS WE'LL

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:10.000
EVER BE.

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:11.000
IT HELPS EXPLAIN WHY SOME

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:13.000
OF THE FIERCEST WARRIORS, LIKE

00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:15.000
ALEXANDER THE GREAT AND JOAN

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:16.000
OF ARC, WERE TEENAGERS, AND WHY

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:18.000
MILITARY RECRUITING STARTS

00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:21.000
AT 17.

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:22.000
TEENS ARE READY TO FIGHT.

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:23.000
HE TOOK ME IN THE BACKYARD.

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.000
IT WAS LIKE BA-BA

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:24.000
IN THE BACKYARD RIGHT THERE.

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:25.000
BOOM, BOOM, BOOM, BOOM, SHOOTIN'

00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:27.000
OFF THE NINE.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:28.000
IT WAS CHILLING.

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:28.000
Reporter: OF COURSE, THIS

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:29.000
PASSION CAN BE TURNED TO BAD

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:31.000
ENDS.

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:32.000
TEENAGERS ALSO COMMIT THREE

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:34.000
TIMES AS MANY CRIMES AS ADULTS.

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:36.000
THESE THREE IN BROOKLYN CLAIM

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:37.000
TO HAVE REFORMED.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:38.000
I MEAN, IF WE ALL KEEP

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:39.000
ON FIGHTING LIKE THIS, WE'RE ALL

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.000
GOING TO BE DEAD.

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:41.000
Reporter: JASON SHOWED US HOW

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:44.000
TO CHOKE PEOPLE TILL THEY PASS

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:45.000
OUT SO YOU CAN STEAL

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:46.000
THEIR MONEY.

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:47.000
DOING BAD THINGS IS JUST FUN.

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:49.000
WHO CARES ABOUT ANYBODY?

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:50.000
WE'RE JUST DOING IT JUST

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.000
TO HAVE FUN.

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:53.000
IT WAS JUST AN ADRENALINE RUSH.

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:53.000
GOING OFF FOR CHASES

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:55.000
WITH THE POLICE.

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:55.000
THEY CAN'T CATCH YOU.

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:57.000
IT'S MAD FUN.

00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:58.000
Reporter: KEEN IS 18.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.000
WE USED TO JUST ROB THEM,

00:11:59.000 --> 00:11:59.000
TAKE THEIR MONEY.

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:00.000
ROB ANOTHER PERSON,

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:01.000
AND THAT'S IT.

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:02.000
GET ZOOTED, GO LOOK FOR GIRLS

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.000
AND HAVE A GOOD TIME.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:05.000
Reporter: DO YOU OWE SOCIETY

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:06.000
ANYTHING?

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:07.000
NOTHING.

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:08.000
WHAT DO I OWE THEM?

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.000
Reporter: PASSION FOR BAD,

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:11.000
OR GOOD.

00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:14.000
EITHER WAY, TEENS TEND TO HAVE

00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:16.000
MORE OF IT THAN WE ADULTS.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:21.000
NOW, DON'T TAKE ME WRONG,

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:22.000
BUT I THINK ADULTS DON'T

00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:24.000
ENJOY LIFE REALLY AS MUCH

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:25.000
AS CHILDREN DO AND THEY TAKE

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:26.000
LIFE FOR GRANTED.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.000
I DON'T THINK ADULTS REALLY KNOW

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.000
WHAT TRUE PASSION IS.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:31.000
Reporter: HMM.

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:32.000
SOME OF US ADULTS MIGHT WANT

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:33.000
TO ARGUE ABOUT THAT.

00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:36.000
BUT IT IS TRUE THAT TEENS ARE

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:39.000
DIFFERENT, IN MANY WAYS.

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.000
HERE AGAIN, JOHN STOSSEL.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.000
IT'S EASY TO GENERALIZE

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:43.000
ABOUT TEENS.

00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:45.000
TALKING ABOUT THEM AS IF THEY'RE

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:46.000
ALL ALIKE, WHEN, OF COURSE,

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:47.000
EVERYONE'S AN INDIVIDUAL.

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:48.000
AND TEENS HATE BEING LABELED

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:49.000
A "TYPE."

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:51.000
THOUGH THAT IS EXACTLY WHAT

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:52.000
THE RESEARCHERS DO HERE,

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.000
AND THEY EARN A GOOD LIVING

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:54.000
DOING IT.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.000
I HAVEN'T HEARD

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:56.000
OF CALVIN KLEIN IN A WHILE.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:57.000
OH, YEAH, YEAH.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:59.000
Reporter: AT TEEN RESEARCH

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.000
UNLIMITED, A PRIVATE MARKET

00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:03.000
RESEARCH FIRM, THEY WATCH TEENS

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:05.000
FROM BEHIND ONE-WAY GLASS.

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:06.000
THE RESEARCHERS ARE COLLECTING

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:07.000
DATA FOR COMPANIES THAT WANT

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:07.000
TO KNOW WHAT KIDS WILL BUY.

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.000
NO!

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:09.000
YES!

00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:11.000
All: NO!

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:12.000
Reporter: BUT THEY'LL WATCH,

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:13.000
WHAT MUSIC THEY LIKE, WHAT

00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.000
THEY'LL WEAR --

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.000
THOSE ARE PRETTY BAGGY.

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:16.000
YEAH.

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:17.000
Reporter: AFTER 16 YEARS

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:18.000
OF WATCHING TEENS, THE PRESIDENT

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:19.000
OF RESEARCH UNLIMITED,

00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:20.000
PETER ZOLLO, HAS COME TO SOME

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.000
CONCLUSIONS ABOUT

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.000
THEIR PERSONALITIES.

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:25.000
WE ACTUALLY SEGMENT TEENS

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:26.000
INTO FOUR DIFFERENT GROUPS.

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:29.000
ONE OF THE GROUPS WE CALL

00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:31.000
INFLUENCERS, WHO ARE THOSE TEENS

00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:33.000
WHO ARE KIND OF AT THE TOP

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:35.000
OF THE TEENAGE SOCIAL HIERARCHY.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:36.000
**

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.000
Reporter: YOU KNOW, THE COOL

00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:39.000
KIDS, THE IN-CROWD.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:41.000
**

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:43.000
THE ONES MANY OF THE OTHER KIDS

00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:44.000
IMITATE AND WANT TO JOIN.

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:48.000
BUT SORRY, MEMBERSHIP IS

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:50.000
BY INVITATION ONLY.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:51.000
FOLLOWING THE INFLUENCERS,

00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:52.000
THERE IS A GROUP WE CALL

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:53.000
THE CONFORMERS.

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:54.000
ALMOST ALL TEENAGERS, HALF

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:57.000
OF TEENAGERS, ARE CONFORMERS.

00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:59.000
THEY'RE LOOKING PARTICULARLY

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.000
UPWARD TOWARDS THE INFLUENCERS

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:01.000
FOR WHAT TO DO, AS FAR AS BEING

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:02.000
THE -- DOING THE LATEST

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:02.000
AND GREATEST.

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.000
Reporter: AFTER

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:04.000
THE CONFORMERS AND

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.000
THE INFLUENCERS COMES ZOLLO'S

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:07.000
GROUP THREE.

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.000
HE CALLS THEM THE PASSIVES,

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:09.000
KIDS --

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.000
-- WHO ARE STRUGGLING

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:12.000
A LITTLE BIT WITH THE SOCIAL

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:14.000
ASPECT OF THIS LIFE STAGE.

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:17.000
HOWEVER, A LOT OF THESE PASSIVES

00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:18.000
ARE HIGH ACHIEVERS IN SCHOOLS.

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:20.000
AND WE CERTAINLY BELIEVE A LOT

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:21.000
OF VERY SUCCESSFUL ADULTS CAME

00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:22.000
FROM THIS GROUP.

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:23.000
THEY'RE NOT AS INVESTED

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.000
IN THE SOCIAL HIERARCHY AS ARE

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:26.000
OTHER TEENS.

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:28.000
I CAN EVEN DRESS MYSELF.

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:29.000
Reporter: 14-YEAR-OLD

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:29.000
O.J. HEIDLER MIGHT FIT THAT

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:32.000
CATEGORY.

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:34.000
O.J. LIVES ON THIS SMALL FARM

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:35.000
IN SOUTH DAKOTA.

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:38.000
HE SAYS WHEN HE GOES OFF TO HIGH

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:39.000
SCHOOL LATER THIS YEAR, HE'S

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:40.000
STILL GOING TO WEAR HIS COWBOY

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:41.000
BOOTS NO MATTER WHAT ANYBODY

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:42.000
SAYS.

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:43.000
I'VE WORE 'EM FOR 14 YEARS

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:45.000
OF MY LIFE.

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:46.000
I SURE AIN'T GONNA CHANGE

00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:48.000
BECAUSE SOMEBODY ELSE SAYS,

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.000
"BOY, THAT LOOKS DUMB."

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:52.000
I DON'T CARE.

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:53.000
Reporter: OF COURSE, WHILE

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.000
THE IN CROWD INFLUENCES,

00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:57.000
THEY RARELY START THE FADS.

00:14:57.000 --> 00:14:58.000
**

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:00.000
THE NEW IDEAS GENERALLY COME

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:02.000
FROM TEENAGE CATEGORY FOUR, WHAT

00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:04.000
ZOLLO CALLS THE EDGE KIDS,

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:05.000
AS IN CUTTING EDGE.

00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:08.000
THE TEENS THEMSELVES MAY CALL

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:10.000
THEMSELVES PUNKS, OR GOTHS,

00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:11.000
OR SURFERS OR SKATERS, DEPENDING

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:12.000
WHERE THEY ARE.

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:14.000
THESE ARE THE MOST REBELLIOUS

00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:15.000
KIDS, TEENS LIKE AURA, WHO SET

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:16.000
THE TRENDS.

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:18.000
NOT ALL THEIR TRENDS ARE

00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:20.000
FOLLOWED.

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:21.000
AND, OF COURSE, TEENS DON'T

00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:22.000
ALWAYS FALL INTO NEAT

00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:23.000
CATEGORIES.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.000
SOME OF THE TEENS TAKING PART

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:27.000
IN THE CHICAGO FOCUS GROUP FELT

00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:28.000
ONE OF THEM, DEE, WAS WHAT ZOLLO

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:29.000
WOULD CALL AN INFLUENCER.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:33.000
SHE'S SO LAID BACK!

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:34.000
I REALLY ADMIRE

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:36.000
HER FOR THE WAY SHE'S LAID BACK.

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:37.000
SHE LOOKS SO PUT TOGETHER.

00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:38.000
Reporter: BUT THEN DEE

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:39.000
REVEALED SOMETHING THAT MIGHT

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:41.000
PUT HER IN THE EDGE CATEGORY.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:44.000
OH, A TONGUE RING.

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:44.000
OH, THAT'S SO COOL!

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:45.000
THAT'S SO COOL.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:46.000
Reporter: WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:48.000
I MEAN, YOU'RE POKING A HOLE

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:48.000
IN YOUR CHIN.

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:51.000
YOUR HAIR IS, I DON'T KNOW WHAT.

00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:52.000
RIGHT.

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:53.000
Reporter: RED.

00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:54.000
PINK.

00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:55.000
Reporter: PINK?

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:56.000
YOU GOT STICKS IN YOUR HAIR.

00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:58.000
WHAT FOR?

00:15:58.000 --> 00:15:59.000
BECAUSE I LIKE IT.

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:00.000
IT'S FUN.

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:01.000
DOESN'T IT MAKE YOU LIKE

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:02.000
SOMEWHAT HAPPY TO LIKE SEE THAT,

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:03.000
INSTEAD OF JUST LIKE THE SAME

00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:04.000
OLD THING YOU SEE EVERY SINGLE

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:05.000
DAY, WALKING DOWN THE STREET.

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:06.000
ALL BLACK, ROBOTIC, BLAH, BLAH,

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:08.000
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:09.000
I MEAN, THAT'S SO, LIKE,

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:11.000
COMMUNIST.

00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:12.000
Reporter: SOMETIMES TEENS

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:14.000
SEEM LIKE PEACOCKS, SHOWING

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:15.000
THEIR FEATHERS, TRYING

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:17.000
TO ATTRACT ATTENTION.

00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:18.000
OR CHAMELEONS, WHO KEEP

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:20.000
EXPERIMENTING WITH DIFFERENT

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:21.000
IDENTITIES, SEARCHING FOR ONE

00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:22.000
THAT FITS.

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:23.000
THIS IS NATURAL, SAY

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:24.000
PSYCHOLOGISTS, ADOLESCENTS NEED

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:25.000
TO DISTANCE THEMSELVES

00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:27.000
FROM THEIR PARENTS

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.000
AND THEIR PARENTS' CUSTOMS.

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:30.000
AS CHILDREN, THEY WERE

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:31.000
SO ATTACHED.

00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:32.000
NOW, IF THEY'RE TO BECOME

00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:33.000
HEALTHY ADULTS, THEY MUST PUSH

00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:35.000
AWAY.

00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:36.000
AREN'T YOU TRYING TO STICK IT

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:38.000
TO US OLD FOLK?

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:39.000
STICK IT HOW?

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:40.000
Reporter: SAY, "LOOK, I DON'T

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:42.000
HAVE TO BE LIKE YOU."

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:43.000
NO, NOT -- COME ON, JOHN.

00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:44.000
WHEN YOU WERE YOUNG, YOU --

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:45.000
YOU WEREN'T LIKE SOME HIPPIE

00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:47.000
KID, WITH LIKE LONG HAIR?

00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:47.000
Reporter: I DIDN'T STICK

00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:49.000
ANY --

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:50.000
AND GOT THROWN OUT OF SCHOOL

00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.000
BECAUSE YOU LIKE WORE THE WRONG

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:51.000
CLOTHES OR SOMETHING?

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:53.000
COME ON.

00:16:53.000 --> 00:16:55.000
**

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:56.000
Reporter: OKAY, SHE HAS

00:16:56.000 --> 00:16:58.000
A POINT.

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:00.000
I GREW UP IN THE '60s.

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:02.000
WE DID LOTS OF THINGS THAT

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:05.000
BUGGED OUR PARENTS.

00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:06.000
BEFORE THAT, THERE WAS GOLDFISH

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:08.000
SWALLOWING AND CRAMMING PHONE

00:17:08.000 --> 00:17:10.000
BOOTHS.

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:11.000
IT'S ALL PART OF THE RITE

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:13.000
OF PASSAGE, THAT NEED TO TRY OUT

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:17.000
NEW PERSONALITIES.

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:18.000
IF IT APPALLS YOUR PARENTS,

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:19.000
SO MUCH THE BETTER, BECAUSE THAT

00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:20.000
PROVES YOU'RE BECOMING

00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:21.000
AN INDIVIDUAL.

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:22.000
WHEN WE COME BACK, SCIENCE SHEDS

00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.000
SOME LIGHT ON TEEN BEHAVIOR.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:27.000
WE LOOK INSIDE A TEENAGE BRAIN.

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:28.000
WHY ARE SO MANY TEENAGERS

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:30.000
SO WEIRD?

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:32.000
IT'S A COMMON COMPLAINT WE HEAR.

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:33.000
THE WAY THEY LOOK, THE WAY

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:34.000
THEY ACT.

00:17:34.000 --> 00:17:36.000
WHAT IT'S ABOUT, SAY

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:37.000
PSYCHOLOGISTS, IS A NECESSARY

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:39.000
BREAKING AWAY FROM US PARENTS,

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.000
A SEPARATION THAT HAS TO HAPPEN

00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:43.000
DURING ADOLESCENCE IF THE TEEN

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:44.000
IS TO BECOME AN INDEPENDENT

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:46.000
ADULT.

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:48.000
IT'S NO LONGER ENOUGH FOR US

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:50.000
TO TELL THEM THE STOVE IS HOT.

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:51.000
NOW, THEY HAVE TO TOUCH IT

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:52.000
TO DECIDE FOR THEMSELVES.

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:53.000
HI, MOM.

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:54.000
I'M SMOKING.

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:55.000
Reporter: WE PARENTS DON'T

00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:56.000
LIKE THAT, BECAUSE

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.000
IN THEIR PURSUIT OF

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:00.000
INDIVIDUALITY, MANY TEENS, NOT

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.000
JUST THE EDGE KIDS, DO CRAZY

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:04.000
THINGS.

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:05.000
**

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:08.000
THEIR MUSIC IS, WELL, DIFFERENT.

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:12.000
AND SOME DON'T JUST LISTEN,

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:13.000
THEY TURN CONCERTS INTO CONTACT

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:14.000
SPORTS.

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:16.000
A FEW ARE DYEING THEIR HAIR,

00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:18.000
PIERCING THEIR TONGUES.

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:20.000
THEY HAVE TO LOOK DIFFERENT,

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:21.000
UNLESS THEY HAVE TO LOOK ALIKE.

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:22.000
BUT THE BIGGEST WORRIES FOR MANY

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:24.000
PARENTS ARE SEXUAL

00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:26.000
EXPERIMENTATION.

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:27.000
BY THE END OF HIGH SCHOOL,

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.000
ABOUT HALF THE TEENS SAY THEY'VE

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:29.000
HAD SEX AND THE PHYSICAL

00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:31.000
RISKTAKING --

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:32.000
HANG ON THERE.

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:33.000
Reporter: O.J. HEIDLER RIDES

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:37.000
BULLS AND ROPES STEER.

00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:39.000
IT'S A TEEN BOY THING.

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:41.000
THE APPARENT RECKLESSNESS,

00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:43.000
DISREGARD FOR PERSONAL SAFETY.

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:44.000
TO ADULTS IT SEEMS AS IF THEY'RE

00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:45.000
NOT JUST DEFYING THE LAWS

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:48.000
OF GRAVITY, BUT COMMON SENSE

00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:49.000
AS WELL.

00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:51.000
**

00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:52.000
IT'S SOMETHING 17-YEAR-OLD

00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:56.000
ALI ZANDI IS KIND OF PROUD OF.

00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:57.000
I'M JUST A CRAZY NUT, A CRAZY

00:18:57.000 --> 00:18:58.000
GUY JUST RUNNING AROUND BREAKING

00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:00.000
THINGS.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:01.000
Reporter: HIS LITTLE BROTHER

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:02.000
CAN'T FIGURE HIM OUT.

00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:04.000
HE'S LIKE WEIRD.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:06.000
HE LISTENS TO CRAZY MUSIC.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:08.000
HE HAS ALL THESE TATTOOS.

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:12.000
I'VE GOT THIS DRAGON RIGHT

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:12.000
HERE, A SKULL, ANOTHER SKULL

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:13.000
OVER HERE.

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:14.000
Reporter: WHY WOULD HE SHOW

00:19:14.000 --> 00:19:15.000
HIS INDEPENDENCE BY GETTING

00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:16.000
PERMANENT TATTOOS?

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:18.000
WELL, THOSE HARVARD RESEARCHERS

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:19.000
WHO DO THE BRAIN SCANS SAY THAT

00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:22.000
NOT ONLY ARE TEENS MORE LIKELY

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:23.000
TO USE THE PART OF THE BRAIN

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:24.000
THAT MAY ALLOW FOR MORE

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:25.000
CREATIVITY, THEY'RE ALSO LESS

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:27.000
LIKELY TO USE THE PART THAT DOES

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:28.000
CRITICAL THINKING.

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:29.000
THAT'S YOUR BRAIN THERE.

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:31.000
Reporter: THAT HELPS PEOPLE

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:32.000
MAKE MATURE JUDGMENTS.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:33.000
TEENS USE THE GUT REACTION PART

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:35.000
OF THE BRAIN.

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:36.000
SO THEY'RE USING THE MORE

00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:37.000
EMOTIONAL, AUTOMATIC PARTS.

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:38.000
MM-HMM.

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:39.000
Reporter: WE SMARTER ADULTS

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:40.000
USE OUR CRITICAL THINKING.

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:43.000
THAT'S EXACTLY RIGHT.

00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:43.000
YOU ACTIVATED MORE UP IN THIS

00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:46.000
REGION.

00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.000
AND THE BOYS THAT WE SAW TODAY

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:48.000
ACTIVATED MORE DOWN IN THIS

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:49.000
REGION.

00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:51.000
Reporter: SO THERE'S A REASON

00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:53.000
FOR US TO WORRY ABOUT THEM?

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:56.000
YES, I THINK SO.

00:19:56.000 --> 00:19:58.000
Reporter: THE BOYS SHE WAS

00:19:58.000 --> 00:19:59.000
TALKING ABOUT INCLUDE THE TEENS

00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:01.000
SHE REGULARLY TESTS, AND NOW

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:03.000
ALSO O.J.

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.000
WE FLEW HIM IN FROM SOUTH DAKOTA

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:06.000
SO HE COULD TAKE THE TEST.

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.000
OKAY.

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:09.000
YOU'RE DOING A SUPER JOB.

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:10.000
THE IMAGES LOOK GREAT.

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:10.000
Reporter: AS PART

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.000
OF THE TEST, AFTER YOU'RE LOADED

00:20:11.000 --> 00:20:14.000
INTO THE MACHINE, THEY HAVE

00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:16.000
YOU LOOK THROUGH A MIRROR

00:20:16.000 --> 00:20:17.000
AT PICTURES OF FACES.

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:18.000
THEN THEY ASK YOU --

00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:19.000
FIGURE OUT THE EXPRESSION

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:20.000
THAT THESE FACES ARE MAKING

00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:21.000
AND I'LL ASK YOU ABOUT THEM WHEN

00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:22.000
YOU COME OUT OF THE MACHINE,

00:20:22.000 --> 00:20:24.000
OKAY?

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:24.000
Reporter: WHAT IS

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:26.000
THE EXPRESSION ON THE FACE?

00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:27.000
THEN THEY WATCH WHICH PART

00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:28.000
OF OUR BRAINS WE USE WHILE

00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:29.000
THINKING ABOUT THAT.

00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:30.000
LATER THEY TEST US FURTHER

00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:31.000
WITH THE SAME FACES.

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:34.000
SHOCKED.

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:37.000
ANGRY.

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:40.000
SAD.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:41.000
HAPPY.

00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:44.000
WHAT THEY'VE FOUND IS THAT

00:20:44.000 --> 00:20:45.000
TEENS, ESPECIALLY THE YOUNGER

00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:46.000
ONES, JUST DON'T SEE THINGS THAT

00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:48.000
ARE OBVIOUS TO US ADULTS.

00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:50.000
NOT SURPRISED?

00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:52.000
NO.

00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:53.000
Reporter: THIS MAN LOOKS

00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:54.000
SHOCKED, ANGUISHED.

00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:55.000
BUT O.J. DOESN'T SEE IT.

00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:56.000
I DON'T THINK THEY HAVE

00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:58.000
A WORD FOR THAT EXPRESSION.

00:20:58.000 --> 00:20:59.000
Reporter: YOU DON'T THINK

00:20:59.000 --> 00:21:01.000
HE'S SHOCKED?

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:03.000
NO.

00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:04.000
Reporter: HE DIDN'T THINK

00:21:04.000 --> 00:21:06.000
THIS WOMAN LOOKED UPSET.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:09.000
YOU DON'T THINK SHE LOOKS SAD?

00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:10.000
SOMETHING BAD JUST HAPPENED?

00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:11.000
NOT THAT BAD, NO.

00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:14.000
Reporter: YURGELUN-TODD SAYS

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:15.000
THIS HELPS EXPLAIN WHY TEENS

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:17.000
OFTEN EXERCISE BAD JUDGMENT.

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:18.000
THEY JUST DON'T SEE WHAT WE SEE.

00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:19.000
THEY MAY NOT REALIZE

00:21:19.000 --> 00:21:22.000
THE TEACHER'S MAD OR THAT

00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:23.000
THEIR GIRLFRIEND'S HURT.

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:25.000
THEIR BRAINS AREN'T ADULT

00:21:25.000 --> 00:21:27.000
OR MATURE AND THEY DON'T YET

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:28.000
HAVE THE WHEREWITHAL TO DO

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:29.000
EVERYTHING WE EXPECT THEM TO DO.

00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:31.000
Reporter: DO YOU THINK THAT

00:21:31.000 --> 00:21:32.000
KIDS YOUR AGE THINK DIFFERENTLY

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:35.000
FROM PEOPLE MY AGE?

00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:36.000
OH, I HOPE SO.

00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:37.000
Reporter: YOU HOPE.

00:21:37.000 --> 00:21:39.000
THAT WOULD BE ONE BIG SCREWED

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:40.000
OFF GROUP IF THAT WAS IT.

00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:42.000
Reporter: THAT'S INSIGHTFUL.

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:45.000
HE UNDERSTANDS THAT TEENS STILL

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:46.000
NEED GUIDANCE FROM PARENTS.

00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:47.000
AND HERE THERE'S SOME GOOD

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:48.000
NEWS --

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:49.000
WHAT'S CERTAINLY DIFFERENT

00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:51.000
ABOUT THESE TEEN GENERATION IS

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:53.000
THEY ARE REALLY FEELING

00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:54.000
A CLOSENESS TO THEIR PARENTS,

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:55.000
MORE SO THAN WE'VE SEEN

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:57.000
IN THE PREVIOUS COUPLE

00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:58.000
OF DECADES.

00:21:58.000 --> 00:22:01.000
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY ARE

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:01.000
THE PEOPLE IN YOUR LIVES THAT

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:02.000
ARE LIKE, ARE THE MOST IMPORTANT

00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:03.000
TO YOU?

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:04.000
MY PARENTS.

00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:04.000
BOTH MY PARENTS.

00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:05.000
MOSTLY MY FATHER.

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:06.000
WHY'S THAT?

00:22:06.000 --> 00:22:07.000
I DON'T KNOW.

00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:08.000
BECAUSE OF HIS INFLUENCE ON ME.

00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:10.000
MY MOM DID A TERRIFIC JOB.

00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:11.000
I REALLY APPRECIATE

00:22:11.000 --> 00:22:12.000
MY PARENTS.

00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:13.000
PARENTS ARE REALLY IMPORTANT

00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:15.000
JUST TO GUIDE YOU AND TELL

00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:16.000
YOU WHAT'S RIGHT AND WRONG.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.000
Reporter: OH, SO THEY DO

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.000
NEED US.

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:22.000
BUT THEN WHY DO SO MANY PARENTS

00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:23.000
COMPLAIN ABOUT SCREAMING FIGHTS

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:25.000
OR SILENCES AND SLAMMED DOORS?

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:27.000
IF TEENS REALLY WANT PARENTS

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:28.000
INVOLVED IN THEIR LIVES, MANY

00:22:28.000 --> 00:22:32.000
ARE HIDING IT WELL.

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:34.000
"WHEN THEY WERE 10,

00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:35.000
THEY OBEYED."

00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:36.000
"NOW, HE WON'T LISTEN."

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:37.000
"HE DOESN'T EVEN SEEM

00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:38.000
TO LIKE ME."

00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:39.000
"IF I TRY TO HELP HER, SHE GOES

00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:44.000
TO HER ROOM AND SLAMS THE DOOR."

00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:46.000
THESE ARE THE KINDS OF THINGS

00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:47.000
PARENTS OF TEENS SAY.

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:49.000
BEWILDERED BY WHAT SEEMS LIKE

00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:50.000
A PERSONALITY CHANGE

00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:51.000
IN THE CHILDREN THEY ONCE KNEW

00:22:51.000 --> 00:22:53.000
SO WELL.

00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:55.000
WHAT CAN A PARENT DO?

00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:58.000
WE HAVE GOT TO ACCEPT

00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:00.000
THE FACT THAT ONCE A KID HITS

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:02.000
ADOLESCENCE, THE WHOLE GAME

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:03.000
CHANGES.

00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:04.000
Reporter: FAMILY THERAPIST

00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:08.000
MIRA KIRSHENBAUM AND

