WORTH IT.

00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:04.000
INSTEAD, FOCUS ON A FEW

00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:06.000
IMPORTANT RULES --

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:08.000
SAY, DON'T DRIVE DRUNK, CALL

00:30:08.000 --> 00:30:09.000
WHEN YOU'RE LATE, DON'T CHEAT.

00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:12.000
WHATEVER'S IMPORTANT TO YOU.

00:30:12.000 --> 00:30:13.000
AFTER THAT, GET OFF YOUR KID'S

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:14.000
BACK.

00:30:14.000 --> 00:30:15.000
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM THAT

00:30:15.000 --> 00:30:17.000
YOU HAVE VALUES.

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:18.000
YOUR VALUES ARE GOOD AND IT'S

00:30:18.000 --> 00:30:20.000
GOOD THAT YOU COMMUNICATE

00:30:20.000 --> 00:30:22.000
YOUR VALUES.

00:30:22.000 --> 00:30:25.000
THE PROBLEM ENTERS WHEN YOU HAVE

00:30:25.000 --> 00:30:27.000
A BUNCH OF LITTLE RULES THAT

00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:28.000
POISON YOUR RELATIONSHIP

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:31.000
WITH YOUR TEENAGER.

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:34.000
DAWN!

00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:36.000
SO YOUR KID GETS SO FED UP

00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:37.000
DEALING WITH YOU, SHE JUST

00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:38.000
WRITES YOU OUT.

00:30:38.000 --> 00:30:40.000
DAWN!

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:41.000
I'M COMING!

00:30:41.000 --> 00:30:42.000
WHEN?

00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:44.000
NEXT YEAR?

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:47.000
YOU EVER FEEL LIKE YOU'RE

00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:48.000
JUST POLICING, DETECTING?

00:30:48.000 --> 00:30:49.000
CONSTANTLY.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:49.000
CONSTANTLY.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:50.000
BECAUSE I CAN'T TRUST HER.

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:51.000
WELL, HOW DO YOU REACT

00:30:51.000 --> 00:30:52.000
TO THAT?

00:30:52.000 --> 00:30:55.000
REBELS.

00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:57.000
I PULL AWAY.

00:30:57.000 --> 00:31:00.000
LIKE HOW?

00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:02.000
I DON'T TELL HER ANYTHING.

00:31:02.000 --> 00:31:03.000
I DON'T DO WHAT I'M SUPPOSED

00:31:03.000 --> 00:31:05.000
TO DO.

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:06.000
I RUN AWAY.

00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:07.000
DO WHATEVER I FEEL LIKE,

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:09.000
WHENEVER I FEEL LIKE IT.

00:31:09.000 --> 00:31:10.000
TEENAGERS, THAT'S THE ESSENCE

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:11.000
OF ADOLESCENCE.

00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:13.000
THEY HAVE AN ALLERGIC REACTION

00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:15.000
TO ANY ATTEMPT TO CONTROL THEM.

00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:17.000
THEY HATE IT, THEY SMELL IT,

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:18.000
AND THEY RUN AWAY FROM IT.

00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:19.000
SO WHAT DO WE DO ABOUT IT?

00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:22.000
WE'LL LOOK

00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:23.000
BY THE TIME OUR KIDS ARE

00:31:23.000 --> 00:31:25.000
TEENS, SOME OF US PARENTS FEEL

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:27.000
AS IF WE NO LONGER HAVE MUCH

00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:28.000
INFLUENCE, THAT THE ONLY PEOPLE

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:30.000
OUR KIDS WILL REALLY LISTEN

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:32.000
TO ARE THEIR PEERS.

00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:32.000
YOU MAKE YOUR FRIENDS MORE

00:31:32.000 --> 00:31:34.000
IMPORTANT THAN ANYTHING ELSE

00:31:34.000 --> 00:31:36.000
IN YOUR LIFE.

00:31:36.000 --> 00:31:36.000
WELL, WHEN I NEED THEM,

00:31:36.000 --> 00:31:37.000
THEY'RE THERE FOR ME MORE THAN

00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:38.000
ANYTHING IN MY LIFE.

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:39.000
OH, NOBODY ELSE DOES NOTHING

00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:39.000
FOR YOU, RIGHT?

00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:45.000
HELL, NO.

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:48.000
WHAT'S UP, YO.

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:49.000
MAD LOVE.

00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:50.000
Reporter: 15-YEAR-OLD MATT

00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:50.000
CAN'T WAIT TO GET OUT

00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:51.000
OF THE HOUSE SO HE CAN BE

00:31:51.000 --> 00:31:52.000
WITH HIS FRIENDS.

00:31:52.000 --> 00:31:52.000
HE SAYS HIS FRIENDS ARE THERE

00:31:52.000 --> 00:31:53.000
FOR HIM.

00:31:53.000 --> 00:31:54.000
THEY ARE!

00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:55.000
THAT'S WHAT YOU GET

00:31:55.000 --> 00:31:56.000
FROM FRIENDS.

00:31:56.000 --> 00:31:57.000
YOU FEEL LIKE YOU BELONG.

00:31:57.000 --> 00:31:58.000
IF HE CAN'T GET IT AT HOME,

00:31:58.000 --> 00:32:00.000
HIS FRIENDS WILL BECOME MORE

00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:03.000
AND MORE IMPORTANT TO HIM.

00:32:03.000 --> 00:32:06.000
THE FRIENDS LISTEN TO YOU.

00:32:06.000 --> 00:32:07.000
WHAT YOU SAY IS OKAY.

00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:08.000
Reporter: MATT AGREES THAT

00:32:08.000 --> 00:32:09.000
HIS FRIENDS REALLY PAY

00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:10.000
ATTENTION.

00:32:10.000 --> 00:32:11.000
MOM DOESN'T.

00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:12.000
SHE DOESN'T LISTEN

00:32:12.000 --> 00:32:13.000
TO ANYTHING I HAVE TO SAY.

00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:14.000
SHE HAS NO TIME TO BE LISTENING

00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:16.000
TO ME.

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:18.000
IF YOU WERE HOME MORE OFTEN,

00:32:18.000 --> 00:32:20.000
YOU COULD SIT AND TALK TO ME.

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:21.000
ONE NIGHT A WEEK, I DON'T WORK,

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:21.000
SATURDAY NIGHT.

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:23.000
WHY DON'T YOU JUST TRY TO STAY

00:32:23.000 --> 00:32:23.000
HOME?

00:32:23.000 --> 00:32:24.000
YEAH, RIGHT, SATURDAY NIGHT.

00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:25.000
NOW, YOU REALLY -- NOW, YOU'RE

00:32:25.000 --> 00:32:26.000
SMOKING CRACK.

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:27.000
SHE WANTS TO SPEND MORE TIME

00:32:27.000 --> 00:32:28.000
WITH HIM.

00:32:28.000 --> 00:32:29.000
PLEASE!

00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:31.000
ONE NIGHT A WEEK.

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:32.000
AND SHE CAN'T GET HIM TO DO IT.

00:32:32.000 --> 00:32:34.000
WELL, OF COURSE NOT.

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:34.000
WHAT DO THEY DO WHEN THEY SPEND

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:36.000
TIME TOGETHER?

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:37.000
THEY FIGHT!

00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:38.000
YOU KNOW WHAT I HAVE TO PUT

00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:39.000
UP THROUGH?

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:43.000
MY NERVES ARE SHOT.

00:32:43.000 --> 00:32:44.000
I'M GONNA EXPLODE ONE DAY

00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:45.000
IF I DON'T GET AWAY.

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:46.000
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

00:32:46.000 --> 00:32:47.000
I'M LEAVING!

00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:48.000
HE'S A REALLY GOOD KID.

00:32:48.000 --> 00:32:49.000
HE WANTS TO WORK IT OUT

00:32:49.000 --> 00:32:50.000
WITH HER.

00:32:50.000 --> 00:32:51.000
HE DOESN'T KNOW HOW.

00:32:51.000 --> 00:32:52.000
Reporter: THE FIRST THING

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:53.000
TO DO, SAY THE EXPERTS, IS

00:32:53.000 --> 00:32:56.000
FOR PARENTS TO LECTURE LESS.

00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:56.000
WHEN I SAY, "I KNOW, DAD,

00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:57.000
I KNOW."

00:32:57.000 --> 00:32:59.000
HE SAYS, "YOU THINK YOU KNOW

00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:00.000
BUT YOU DON'T KNOW.

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:01.000
YOU DON'T KNOW!"

00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:01.000
AND I'M LIKE, "BUT DAD, I --

00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:02.000
I KNOW."

00:33:02.000 --> 00:33:03.000
HE SAYS, "NO, YOU DON'T KNOW.

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:05.000
'CAUSE IF YOU KNEW, YOU WOULDN'T

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:06.000
HAVE DONE IT!"

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:07.000
YOU KNOW, I'M REALLY MORE

00:33:07.000 --> 00:33:08.000
AFRAID OF BEING LECTURED THAN

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:09.000
BEING PUNISHED, BECAUSE IT'S

00:33:09.000 --> 00:33:10.000
JUST REALLY REDUNDANT

00:33:10.000 --> 00:33:11.000
AND TEDIOUS AND ALL.

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:13.000
ASK YOURSELF AS A PARENT, WHY

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:15.000
DON'T YOU LISTEN TO PEOPLE?

00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:16.000
WELL, YOU DON'T LISTEN

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:17.000
TO SOMEONE FOR ONE REASON,

00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:19.000
BECAUSE THEY TELL YOU THE SAME

00:33:19.000 --> 00:33:20.000
THING OVER AND OVER AND OVER.

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.000
YOU'VE HEARD IT 20 TIMES.

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:22.000
WHY WOULD YOU LISTEN TO IT

00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:24.000
THE 21st TIME?

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:26.000
DOES, LIKE, LECTURING JUST

00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:27.000
COME NATURALLY NOW THAT YOU'RE

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:29.000
A PARENT, YOU LIKE TO LECTURE?

00:33:29.000 --> 00:33:30.000
Reporter: I THINK I KNOW MORE

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:30.000
THAN YOU.

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:31.000
YOU'RE A KID.

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:33.000
AS KIDS, WE THINK WE KNOW

00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:36.000
MORE THAN YOU.

00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:36.000
Reporter: BUT YOU DON'T.

00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:37.000
BUT WE DON'T.

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:38.000
BUT BY YOU TELLING US WHAT WE DO

00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:39.000
AND DON'T KNOW ISN'T GONNA

00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:39.000
HELP US.

00:33:39.000 --> 00:33:40.000
Reporter: IT ISN'T GOING

00:33:40.000 --> 00:33:41.000
TO HELP THEM FORM THEIR OWN

00:33:41.000 --> 00:33:43.000
IDENTITIES.

00:33:43.000 --> 00:33:44.000
AND IT MAY PUSH THEM AWAY.

00:33:44.000 --> 00:33:45.000
INSTEAD OF MAKING THIS POCKET

00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:46.000
FLAT --

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:47.000
Reporter: AURA'S PARENTS

00:33:47.000 --> 00:33:48.000
PUSHED HER AWAY BY ATTACKING

00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:50.000
THE VERY THING THAT TURNED OUT

00:33:50.000 --> 00:33:51.000
TO MAKE HER SUCCESSFUL.

00:33:51.000 --> 00:33:53.000
MY PARENTS HATED THE WAY

00:33:53.000 --> 00:33:54.000
I DRESSED, HATED IT.

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:55.000
Reporter: WHAT DID THEY SAY?

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:56.000
THEY HATED THE MAKEUP.

00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:58.000
THEY HATED LIKE THE CRAZY

00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:00.000
HAIRSTYLES.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:02.000
Reporter: THE RESULT?

00:34:02.000 --> 00:34:04.000
SHE MOVED IN WITH HER BOYFRIEND.

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:05.000
MIRA KIRSHENBAUM SAYS RATHER

00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:06.000
THAN LECTURE YOUR TEEN --

00:34:06.000 --> 00:34:08.000
ASK QUESTIONS.

00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:09.000
LISTEN, LISTEN, LISTEN.

00:34:09.000 --> 00:34:10.000
Reporter: WELL, I'M

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:11.000
THE PARENT, WHAT CAN

00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:12.000
SHE TELL ME?

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:14.000
I'M SUPPOSED TO TEACH HER.

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:16.000
WHY SHOULD SHE LISTEN TO YOU?

00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:17.000
YOU HAVEN'T EARNED THE RIGHT.

00:34:17.000 --> 00:34:18.000
Reporter: WHAT DO YOU MEAN,

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:18.000
EARN IT?

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:20.000
I'M HER PARENT.

00:34:20.000 --> 00:34:21.000
I DON'T HAVE TO EARN IT.

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:23.000
IF YOU ASK HER THE QUESTIONS

00:34:23.000 --> 00:34:25.000
ABOUT HOW SHE FELT AND WHY

00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:27.000
SHE DID IT AND WHAT IT MEANT,

00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:29.000
SHE'S GOING TO FEEL THAT YOU ARE

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:32.000
A SAFE PERSON TO TELL THINGS TO.

00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:33.000
THEN YOU CAN SAY, "CAN I TELL

00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:35.000
YOU HOW I FEEL?"

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:36.000
WELL, YOU -- FIRST OF ALL,

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:38.000
YOU'VE EARNED THE RIGHT NOW

00:34:38.000 --> 00:34:39.000
TO TALK ABOUT HOW YOU FEEL

00:34:39.000 --> 00:34:40.000
BECAUSE SHE'S OPENED UP.

00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:41.000
AND THAT'S HOW PARENTS WHO

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:43.000
REALLY DO HAVE INFLUENCE

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:44.000
WITH THEIR KIDS GET INFLUENCE,

00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:46.000
IS BY LISTENING TO

00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:48.000
THEIR TEENAGERS TALK FIRST.

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:50.000
WHY DID I DO IT?

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:51.000
BECAUSE I REALLY DIDN'T WANT

00:34:51.000 --> 00:34:52.000
TO GO TO SCHOOL.

00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:53.000
Reporter: THEN YOU CAN SAY

00:34:53.000 --> 00:34:54.000
WHAT YOU WOULD DO, WHAT

00:34:54.000 --> 00:34:55.000
YOUR VALUES ARE.

00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:56.000
WHERE ARE YOU GOING TO GET

00:34:56.000 --> 00:34:57.000
WITHOUT SCHOOL?

00:34:57.000 --> 00:34:58.000
NOWHERE.

00:34:58.000 --> 00:34:59.000
Reporter: THE TEENS MAY NOT

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:00.000
ACT LIKE THEY HEAR IT,

00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:01.000
BUT THE EXPERTS SAY THEY DO,

00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:02.000
AND IT WILL MAKE A DIFFERENCE

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:03.000
LATER.

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:06.000
AFTER ALL, SURVEYS SHOW MOST

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:08.000
YOUNG ADULTS EVENTUALLY DO ADOPT

00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:10.000
THEIR PARENTS' VALUES.

00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:11.000
YOU JUST CAN'T FORCE IT.

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:13.000
ON THE OTHER HAND, WHILE BEING

00:35:13.000 --> 00:35:15.000
VERY STRICT, TOO CONTROLLING,

00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:16.000
CAUSES PROBLEMS, THE OPPOSITE

00:35:16.000 --> 00:35:18.000
CAUSES PROBLEMS, TOO.

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:19.000
REMEMBER BEN MULLIGAN,

00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:20.000
THE 18-YEAR-OLD WHO BEAT ME

00:35:20.000 --> 00:35:22.000
ON THE AEROBIC TEST?

00:35:22.000 --> 00:35:24.000
WE FIRST MET HIM HERE IN MAINE,

00:35:24.000 --> 00:35:25.000
AT THE HYDE SCHOOL, A SCHOOL

00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:26.000
THAT SPECIALIZES IN HELPING

00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:27.000
TEENAGERS WHO ARE HAVING

00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:29.000
PROBLEMS.

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:30.000
BEN'S PARENTS BROUGHT HIM HERE

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:32.000
BECAUSE HE'D BEEN GETTING STONED

00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:34.000
AND HIS GRADES HAD FALLEN.

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.000
BEN WAS EXTREMELY UNHAPPY

00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:36.000
AND HE WAS VERY REBELLIOUS.

00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:37.000
LIKE A LOT OF DRINKING

00:35:37.000 --> 00:35:39.000
OVER THAT SUMMER, SMOKED A LOT

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:41.000
OF POT.

00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:42.000
YOU KNOW, MY FAULT IN THAT

00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:44.000
WAS I DISENGAGED.

00:35:44.000 --> 00:35:45.000
Reporter: BEN'S FATHER FEARED

00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:46.000
THE TRUTH, SO HE DIDN'T ASK.

00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:47.000
I MEAN, I WOULDN'T ASK THOSE

00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:49.000
HARD QUESTIONS, EVER.

00:35:49.000 --> 00:35:52.000
I BECAME LAZY.

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:54.000
ABDICATING JUST BASICALLY

00:35:54.000 --> 00:35:55.000
SAYS TO YOUR KID, "YOU KNOW,

00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:56.000
I DON'T CARE."

00:35:56.000 --> 00:35:58.000
AND THAT'S TERRIBLE.

00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:00.000
ONE OF THE MARKS OF A REALLY

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:02.000
GOOD PARENT IS THAT YOU ASK

00:36:02.000 --> 00:36:04.000
QUESTIONS THAT GET BAD NEWS.

00:36:04.000 --> 00:36:06.000
IF YOU'RE NOT HEARING BAD NEWS,

00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:07.000
YOUR KID'S NOT TELLING

00:36:07.000 --> 00:36:08.000
YOU THE WHOLE TRUTH.

00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:09.000
Reporter: BUT HOW MUCH

00:36:09.000 --> 00:36:10.000
INFLUENCE DO WE HAVE OVER THESE

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:12.000
KIDS ANYWAY?

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:14.000
YOU HAVE AN ENORMOUS AMOUNT

00:36:14.000 --> 00:36:15.000
OF INFLUENCE FOR A COUPLE

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:17.000
OF REASONS.

00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:20.000
DEEP DOWN YOUR KID IS FEELING

00:36:20.000 --> 00:36:23.000
UNLOVED AND SCARED.

00:36:23.000 --> 00:36:25.000
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN SO SCARED

00:36:25.000 --> 00:36:26.000
OF, YOU KNOW, WHAT AM I GONNA DO

00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:27.000
WITH MY LIFE?

00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:28.000
I REALLY WISH I WAS, LIKE,

00:36:28.000 --> 00:36:30.000
A LOT CLOSER WITH MY DAD

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:31.000
ESPECIALLY, BECAUSE HE, LIKE,

00:36:31.000 --> 00:36:33.000
GETS HOME FROM WORK AT, LIKE,

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:34.000
5:00 OR 6:00 AND THEN HE GOES

00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:36.000
INTO HIS, LIKE, ROOM AND WATCHES

00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:37.000
BASKETBALL AND FOOTBALL

00:36:37.000 --> 00:36:38.000
OR WHATEVER SEASON IT IS.

00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:39.000
Reporter: IS THE MOST

00:36:39.000 --> 00:36:40.000
IMPORTANT RELATIONSHIP YOU HAVE

00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:42.000
IN YOUR LIFE WITH YOUR PARENTS?

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:43.000
YES?

00:36:43.000 --> 00:36:44.000
TEENAGERS MAY NOT SHOW IT,

00:36:44.000 --> 00:36:45.000
BUT THEY DO WANT QUESTIONS,

00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:47.000
INTEREST, LIMITS.

00:36:47.000 --> 00:36:48.000
IT MAKES THEM FEEL SAFE

00:36:48.000 --> 00:36:49.000
AND LOVED.

00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.000
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES I WISH

00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:52.000
THAT THEY WOULD BE MORE STRICT,

00:36:52.000 --> 00:36:53.000
LIKE, YOU KNOW, SET A LITTLE

00:36:53.000 --> 00:36:54.000
MORE RULES.

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:55.000
I KNOW I'M GOING TO REGRET THIS

00:36:55.000 --> 00:36:57.000
IN TWO MONTHS, BUT STILL --

00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:59.000
Reporter: I WAS SURPRISED HOW

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.000
MANY TEENS TOLD ME THEY LIKED IT

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:02.000
WHEN THEIR PARENTS SET LIMITS.

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:03.000
WHY WOULD YOU WANT THEM TO BE

00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:04.000
MORE STRICT?

00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:05.000
THAT WOULD TAKE AWAY

00:37:05.000 --> 00:37:07.000
YOUR FREEDOM.

00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:09.000
BECAUSE IF THEY'RE MORE

00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:10.000
STRICT, THEN, LIKE,

00:37:10.000 --> 00:37:10.000
THEY PARTICIPATE MORE

00:37:10.000 --> 00:37:13.000
IN MY LIFE.

00:37:13.000 --> 00:37:14.000
Reporter: AND PARTICIPATION

00:37:14.000 --> 00:37:15.000
ISN'T JUST SETTING LIMITS.

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:17.000
ONE TRICK, SAY THE EXPERTS, IS

00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:18.000
CATCH YOUR CHILD DOING SOMETHING

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:20.000
RIGHT.

00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:21.000
IN OTHER WORDS, SEEK OUT THINGS

00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:22.000
TO PRAISE.

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:24.000
THANKS SO MUCH.

00:37:24.000 --> 00:37:25.000
FOR EXAMPLE, IT MEANT A LOT

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:27.000
TO ME WHEN YOU TOOK OUT

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:28.000
THE GARBAGE WITHOUT MY EVEN

00:37:28.000 --> 00:37:29.000
ASKING.

00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:31.000
THANKS.

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:31.000
IT MAKES MY LIFE EASIER.

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:32.000
Reporter: BUT HE OUGHT

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:33.000
TO TAKE OUT THE GARBAGE.

00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:34.000
I HAVE TO PRAISE HIM FOR TAKING

00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:35.000
OUT THE GARBAGE?

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:36.000
YEAH.

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:37.000
Reporter: IT'S NOT REALLY

00:37:37.000 --> 00:37:38.000
NATURAL TO DO THAT.

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:41.000
IT'S MUCH MORE NATURAL TO SPEAK

00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:42.000
UP WHEN HE DOESN'T TAKE OUT

00:37:42.000 --> 00:37:43.000
THE GARBAGE.

00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:44.000
TOUGH NOOGIES.

00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:45.000
IF YOU KEEP FOCUSING

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:47.000
ON THE CRITICISM, THAT'S ALL

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:48.000
YOUR KID WILL HEAR, THAT'S ALL

00:37:48.000 --> 00:37:50.000
THE WHOLE -- YOU'RE POLLUTING

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:51.000
YOUR FAMILY ENVIRONMENT.

00:37:51.000 --> 00:37:53.000
Reporter: AT THE HYDE SCHOOL,

00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:54.000
PARENTS MUST ATTEND PERIODIC

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:55.000
MEETINGS WHERE THEY'RE TAUGHT

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:56.000
MUCH OF WHAT YOU'VE HEARD THIS

00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:58.000
HOUR.

00:37:58.000 --> 00:37:59.000
YES, THERE MUST BE RULES,

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:01.000
BUT THE RULES SHOULD BE FEW,

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:02.000
TO ALLOW TEENS ROOM TO MAKE

00:38:02.000 --> 00:38:04.000
THEIR OWN MISTAKES.

00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:06.000
ABOVE ALL, THEY SAY, LECTURE

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:08.000
LESS AND LISTEN MORE.

00:38:08.000 --> 00:38:09.000
LORI BROUGHT ASHLEY HERE.

00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:12.000
FOR ME, IT'S LEARNING

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:13.000
TO LISTEN WITH MY MOUTH CLOSED

00:38:13.000 --> 00:38:14.000
AND MY EARS OPEN, AND THAT

00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:16.000
SHE MAY HAVE A LOT MORE WISDOM

00:38:16.000 --> 00:38:17.000
THAN I GIVE HER CREDIT FOR.

00:38:17.000 --> 00:38:19.000
Reporter: BEN'S MOM NOW

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:21.000
ADMITS THAT SHE'D FORGOTTEN

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:22.000
THE REAL GOAL IN PARENTING

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:25.000
A TEEN.

00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:27.000
THEY WILL BE INDIVIDUALS

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:28.000
WITHOUT ME, AND THAT AFTER ALL

00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:30.000
IS THE GOAL IS TO RAISE

00:38:30.000 --> 00:38:31.000
OUR CHILDREN TO BE

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:32.000
SELF-SUFFICIENT.

00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:33.000
Reporter: THEY'RE ALMOST

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:34.000
ADULTS, PARENTS ARE REMINDED.

00:38:34.000 --> 00:38:36.000
YOU CAN SHOW THEM WHAT

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:38.000
YOUR VALUES ARE, BUT YOU CAN'T

00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:39.000
CONTROL THEM ANYMORE.

00:38:39.000 --> 00:38:43.000
SO JUST LOVE THEM AND LISTEN

00:38:43.000 --> 00:38:44.000
TO THEM, AND WITH LUCK, THEY'LL

00:38:44.000 --> 00:38:45.000
LET YOU INTO THEIR LIVES.

00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:46.000
THAT'S HOW YOU KNOW YOU'RE

00:38:46.000 --> 00:38:48.000
A SUCCESSFUL PARENT --

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:49.000
IF YOUR KID WILL TELL

00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:51.000
YOU ANYTHING.

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:53.000
THAT SAVES KIDS' LIVES.

00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:54.000
YOU SHOULD PUT UP A BANNER

00:38:54.000 --> 00:38:56.000
IN YOUR LIVING ROOM THAT SAYS,

00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:58.000
"WE CAN TALK ABOUT ANYTHING

00:38:58.000 --> 00:38:59.000
HERE."

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:00.000
I'LL BE BACK WITH SOME FINAL

00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:05.000
THOUGHTS, AFTER THIS.

00:39:05.000 --> 00:39:06.000
AS I LISTENED TO THE FAMILY

00:39:06.000 --> 00:39:08.000
THERAPISTS TALK ABOUT GIVING

00:39:08.000 --> 00:39:09.000
OUR TEENS ROOM, NOT BEING

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:11.000
SO STRICT, IT SOUNDED LIKE WE'RE

00:39:11.000 --> 00:39:13.000
SUPPOSED TO BE OUR TEENS'

00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:14.000
FRIENDS.

00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:15.000
BUT THE EXPERTS SAID, "NO, WHY

00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:16.000
WOULD YOU WANT TO BE YOUR KID'S

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:17.000
FRIEND?

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:19.000
THEY DON'T KNOW ANYTHING,

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:21.000
AND THEIR MUSIC'S LOUSY."

00:39:21.000 --> 00:39:22.000
INSTEAD, THEY SAID, BE AN ALLY.

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:24.000
SOMEONE WHO OFFERS HELP,

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:26.000
BUT DOESN'T TRY TO CONTROL.

00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:28.000
FINALLY, THEY SAID, IF THEY'RE

00:39:28.000 --> 00:39:29.000
DISOBEDIENT DURING THESE YEARS,

00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:30.000
REMEMBER, THEY'LL USUALLY GROW

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:32.000
OUT OF IT.

00:39:32.000 --> 00:39:33.000
THEY MAY INFURIATE YOU NOW,

00:39:33.000 --> 00:39:34.000
BUT IN A FEW YEARS, THEY'LL BE

00:39:34.000 --> 00:39:36.000
BACK.

00:39:36.000 --> 00:39:37.000
AND IF THEY THEN THINK

00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:39.000
OF YOU AS AN ALLY, THEY WILL

00:39:39.000 --> 00:39:40.000
ALWAYS WANT TO BE PART

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:41.000
OF YOUR LIFE.

00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:42.000
THAT'S OUR PROGRAM FOR TONIGHT.

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:44.000
I'LL BE BACK THIS THURSDAY

00:39:44.000 --> 00:39:45.000
WITH A SPECIAL ABOUT AMBITION.

00:39:45.000 --> 00:39:47.000
I CALL IT "GREED."

